4th September 2018. I could write how beautiful is life or smth simmilar, but I won’t. Life is beautiful, yes. But not always. Especially if you have insecurities. I know how it feels to have them, bcs that leaded me all my life, even from childhood: I was too tall and skinny, I didn’t know where to put my legs or arms, how to stand bcs in every pose I looked strange. When I became teen other “problems” appeared. But let’s be real- you are human. That’s mean you drink water, you eat food. Ofc after that your belly will be bigger. It has to be like that. And you have to love it, bcs your body is healthy. You don’t have to put yourself in some numbers. I’m a model- I have to. But I’m human also. My waist usually is 60-62. Last Monday it was 64.5. Why? Bcs all week I had a cold and drank so many medicines. Ofc my metabolism became slower. And I’m not going to start starving. God no. Sport and healthy food. And not just 3 times per day. I’m still growing. I’m becaming a woman and I want to be mother one day. So NO diets. Love your body. It deserves that. You want some changes? Start workouts, eat healthy. But EAT. Ofc we are putting in social media everything what is the best and the most beautiful, but it’s 21st century. Let’s talk some real bcs otherwise- I’m scared in what kind of world my little niece and future daughter will live.
#body #selflove #reality
